el documentarians, photojournalists, fine artists, hobbyists, and photographic printers – from Lucy Maude Montgomery on Prince Edward Island to Élise Livernois in Quebec City, and from Margaret Bourke-White in the Arctic to Hannah Maynard on Vancouver Island. Why women? Why not women? Presenting the exceptional range and impact of their work, Rare Merit proves that women’s practices and images – knowingly omitted from founding narratives of photographic history – were diverse, compelling, widespread, and influential.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPhotographyzCanadaxHistoryy19th century. 0aPhotographyzCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aPortrait photographyzCanadaxHistoryy19th century. 0aPortrait photographyzCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aWomen photographerszCanadavBiography. 0aWomen photographerszCanadaxHistoryy19th century. 0aWomen photographerszCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 7aPhotography / History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311127214608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022z978311127419508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311141763940uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077486706140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774867061423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774867061/original  a978-3-11-127214-6  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-127419-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-141763-9  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles